 that is deactivated by dipeptidyl peptidase-4 (DPP-IV). DPP-IV inhibitors work by preventing the breakdown of GLP-1, thereby enhancing its activity. This leads to increased insulin secretion and improved glucose control in patients with type 2 diabetes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECholecystokinin (CCK)\u003C/strong\u003E is a hormone that stimulates the digestion of fat and protein. It is not directly affected by DPP-IV.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPeptide YY (PYY)\u003C/strong\u003E is a hormone involved in reducing appetite and inhibiting gastric motility. It is not a target of DPP-IV.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInsulin\u003C/strong\u003E is a hormone produced by the pancreas that regulates blood glucose levels. While GLP-1 enhances insulin secretion, insulin itself is not directly deactivated by DPP-IV.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGhrelin\u003C/strong\u003E is a hormone that stimulates appetite, often referred to as the \u0027hunger hormone\u0027. It is not affected by DPP-IV.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Dipeptidyl peptidase-4 (DPP-IV) inhibitors work by preventing the breakdown of incretin hormones, thereby enhancing their activity.","Glucagon-like peptide-1 (GLP-1) is an incretin hormone that is deactivated by DPP-IV.","Increased levels of GLP-1 lead to improved insulin secretion and glucose control."],"references":["Bender, D. A., \u0026 Cunningham, S. M. (2021). Introduction to nutrition and metabolism. CRC Press","Salway, J. G. (2016). Metabolism at a Glance. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Judge A, Dodd MS. Metabolism. Essays Biochem. 2020 Oct 8;64(4):607-647. doi: 10.1042/EBC20190041. PMID: 32830223; PMCID: PMC7545035Pathak R, Bridgeman MB. Dipeptidyl Peptidase-4 (DPP-4) Inhibitors In the Management of Diabetes. P T. 2010 Sep;35(9):509-13. PMID: 20975810; PMCID: PMC2957740.","Gallwitz B. Clinical Use of DPP-4 Inhibitors. Front Endocrinol (Lausanne). 2019 